HEADWORD: Hoveler
<hw>Hov"el*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who assists in
saving life and property from a wreck; a coast boatman.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hoveller</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>G. P. R. James.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

